Package: phasic
Type: Package
Title: Phase-Type Distribution Algorithms
Version: 0.22.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Kasper", "Munch", email = "kaspermunch@birc.au.dk", role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Tobias", "Røikjer", role = "aut"),
    person("Asger", "Hobolth", role = "aut")
  )
Description: High-performance library for computing with phase-type distributions
    using graph-based algorithms. Provides R interface to Python implementation
    via 'reticulate'. Phase-type distributions model time until absorption in
    continuous or discrete-time Markov chains. Includes methods for graph
    construction via create_graph(), reward transformation, moment computation,
    trace-based elimination with record_elimination_trace(), and Bayesian
    inference via Stein Variational Gradient Descent (SVGD). Implements
    algorithms from Røikjer, Hobolth & Munch (2022) <doi:10.1007/s11222-022-10155-6>.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
URL: https://github.com/munch-group/phasic
BugReports: https://github.com/munch-group/phasic/issues
